on public protection. It provides a detailed exploration of MAPPA policy and practice in order to prompt further debate about the implications of the risk paradigm for young people and youth justice practitioners. In the book, key academics, practitioners and policy makers consider a range of theoretical and practical issues raised by the introduction of MAPPA including risk and children's rights, the use of professional discretion by practitioners, alternative approaches to risk management and suggestions for future policy development. It will be of interest to both professionals and academics working with young offenders and in youth justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzGreat Britain. 0aJuvenile delinquencyzGreat Britain. 0aJuvenile justice, Administration ofzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aBaker, Kerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaker, Kerry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJones, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemshall, Hazel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcNeill, Fergus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonk, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutherland, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutherland, Alex, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWhitty, Noel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWood, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978184742215640uhtt